==English==

===Etymology===
Italian [[:it:maneggiare|maneggiare]] "handle, manage", from Vulgar Latin ''*manidiare'' "handle" (whence also Spanish [[:es:manejar|manejar]]), derived from Latin [[manus]] "hand". It is akin to French [[:fr:manier|manier]] "handle", and probably Korean [[:ko:마니다|마니다]] (manida), [[:ko:만지다|만지다]] (manjida) "handle", and [[:ko:만들다|만들다]] (mandeulda) "make".

